    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Automate a routine task with HTTP / REST API and Airtable end to end\n\n**Pattern:** Workflow Automation · **Level:** Advanced · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nAutomate a routine task with HTTP / REST API and Airtable end to end. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual helpers is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nWeekly Schedule → Map to Canonical Schema → Route by Event Kind → Handle 'job.start' → Airtable → Consolidate Handling → Sort Payloads Newest First → Stamp Processing Time → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to workflow automation without manual effort\n- Anyone automating helpers in software development\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Scales without extra headcount\n- Saves hours of manual work each week\n- Has retries and error handling built in\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Airtable PAT; Slack OAuth2; Twilio SID + token.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "22e184e5-3392-fb72-031c-13ed393bc974",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
